[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":877},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F11\u002F27\u002Fantfu-ni-replace-npm-yarn-pnpm-bun\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F11\u002F27\u002Fantfu-ni-replace-npm-yarn-pnpm-bun\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F11\u002F27\u002Fantfu-ni-replace-npm-yarn-pnpm-bun\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F11\u002F27\u002Fantfu-ni-replace-npm-yarn-pnpm-bun\u002F":852,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F11\u002F27\u002Fantfu-ni-replace-npm-yarn-pnpm-bun\u002F":861},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20221127\u002F2847196536\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":832,"date":833,"description":834,"extension":835,"lang":836,"meta":837,"navigation":838,"path":839,"readingMinutes":840,"seo":841,"standalone":842,"stem":843,"tags":844,"tldr":848,"updated":849,"url":850,"__hash__":851},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fantfu-ni-replace-npm-yarn-pnpm-bun.md","One ni to Rule Them All? Replace npm\u002Fyarn\u002Fpnpm\u002Fbun with antfu\u002Fni","8471965325",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":813},"minimark",[11,19,24,40,47,61,64,67,76,91,113,119,125,153,164,169,175,185,191,197,235,238,243,255,288,299,311,314,353,357,367,397,404,443,449,453,471,506,512,516,524,556,561,565,577,617,624,671,675,683,721,725,733,748,752,764,786,797,801,809],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"Various package managers","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002Fni.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26,27,31,32,35,36,39],{},"Ever wondered — when you pick up someone else's project, do you run ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"npm install"," or ",[28,33,34],{},"yarn install","? With so many package installers out there, you have to peek inside the project every time. This post introduces a really clever package installer — ",[28,37,38],{},"antfu\u002Fni",".",[20,41,43,44,46],{"id":42},"what-is-antfuni","What is ",[28,45,38],{},"?",[12,48,49,50,52,53,60],{},"What's ",[28,51,38],{},"? It's a package manager built by the well-known ",[54,55,59],"a",{"href":56,"rel":57},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fantfu-collective\u002Fni",[58],"nofollow","antfu",". At this point you might be thinking:",[12,62,63],{},"\"Wait — yet another command set to memorize?!\"",[12,65,66],{},"Hold on, let me explain.",[12,68,69,70,72,73,75],{},"The point of ",[28,71,38],{}," is that you can use it in any project — no more peeking at the project to figure out which package manager it uses. Just type ",[28,74,38],{}," and you're done.",[12,77,78,79,82,83,85,86,82,89,39],{},"For example, when you pick up a project, you'd usually open it to check the package manager. If it's ",[28,80,81],{},"npm",", you'd run ",[28,84,30],{}," to restore the project. If it's ",[28,87,88],{},"yarn",[28,90,34],{},[12,92,93,94,97,98,101,102,105,106,109,110,112],{},"But now there are so many package managers — ",[28,95,96],{},"pnpm",", ",[28,99,100],{},"bun",", and so on — each with their own commands. yarn installs packages with ",[28,103,104],{},"yarn add [plugin name]",", npm uses ",[28,107,108],{},"npm install [plugin name]",", etc. Our brains have limited memory, so ",[28,111,38],{}," solves this problem.",[20,114,116,117],{"id":115},"how-to-use-antfuni","How to use ",[28,118,38],{},[12,120,121,122,124],{},"First, install ",[28,123,38],{}," globally:",[126,127,132],"pre",{"className":128,"code":129,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","npm i -g @antfu\u002Fni\n","bash","",[28,133,134],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,136,139,142,146,150],"span",{"class":137,"line":138},"line",1,[135,140,81],{"class":141},"s_sBn",[135,143,145],{"class":144},"sTRMh"," i",[135,147,149],{"class":148},"sCcAr"," -g",[135,151,152],{"class":144}," @antfu\u002Fni\n",[12,154,155,156,159,160,163],{},"Then open your terminal, ",[28,157,158],{},"cd"," into your project, and type ",[28,161,162],{},"ni",". It auto-detects and installs everything. Magic, right?",[12,165,166],{},[15,167],{"alt":162,"src":168},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVX6K8sh.png",[12,170,171,172,174],{},"How does ",[28,173,162],{}," work? It checks your lockfile to decide which installer to use. The lockfile is what you usually see in your project — package-lock.json, pnpm-lock.yaml, yarn.lock, bun.lockb.",[12,176,177,178,180,181,184],{},"Without a lockfile, ",[28,179,162],{}," checks ",[28,182,183],{},"packageManager"," in package.json to pick the installer. But you should always have a lockfile.",[20,186,188,190],{"id":187},"ni-commands",[28,189,162],{}," commands",[12,192,193,194,196],{},"What commands does ",[28,195,162],{}," have? These:",[198,199,200,205,210,215,220,225,230],"ul",{},[201,202,203],"li",{},[28,204,162],{},[201,206,207],{},[28,208,209],{},"nr",[201,211,212],{},[28,213,214],{},"nx",[201,216,217],{},[28,218,219],{},"nu",[201,221,222],{},[28,223,224],{},"nun",[201,226,227],{},[28,228,229],{},"nci",[201,231,232],{},[28,233,234],{},"na",[12,236,237],{},"Look cryptic, but each maps to a specific action. Let me walk through them.",[239,240,241],"h3",{"id":162},[28,242,162],{},[12,244,245,247,248,251,252,254],{},[28,246,162],{}," means ",[28,249,250],{},"install",". So typing ",[28,253,162],{}," equals:",[126,256,258],{"className":128,"code":257,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm install\nyarn install\npnpm install\nbun install\n",[28,259,260,267,274,281],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,261,262,264],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,263,81],{"class":141},[135,265,266],{"class":144}," install\n",[135,268,270,272],{"class":137,"line":269},2,[135,271,88],{"class":141},[135,273,266],{"class":144},[135,275,277,279],{"class":137,"line":276},3,[135,278,96],{"class":141},[135,280,266],{"class":144},[135,282,284,286],{"class":137,"line":283},4,[135,285,100],{"class":141},[135,287,266],{"class":144},[12,289,290,291,294,295,298],{},"To install a specific package, run ",[28,292,293],{},"ni [plugin name]",". To install ",[28,296,297],{},"express",":",[126,300,302],{"className":128,"code":301,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"ni express\n",[28,303,304],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,305,306,308],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,307,162],{"class":141},[135,309,310],{"class":144}," express\n",[12,312,313],{},"Which equals:",[126,315,317],{"className":128,"code":316,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm install express\nyarn add express\npnpm add express\nbun add express\n",[28,318,319,328,337,345],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,320,321,323,326],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,322,81],{"class":141},[135,324,325],{"class":144}," install",[135,327,310],{"class":144},[135,329,330,332,335],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,331,88],{"class":141},[135,333,334],{"class":144}," add",[135,336,310],{"class":144},[135,338,339,341,343],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,340,96],{"class":141},[135,342,334],{"class":144},[135,344,310],{"class":144},[135,346,347,349,351],{"class":137,"line":283},[135,348,100],{"class":141},[135,350,334],{"class":144},[135,352,310],{"class":144},[239,354,355],{"id":209},[28,356,209],{},[12,358,359,247,361,364,365,254],{},[28,360,209],{},[28,362,363],{},"run",". So ",[28,366,209],{},[126,368,370],{"className":128,"code":369,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm run\nyarn run\npnpm run\nbun run\n",[28,371,372,379,385,391],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,373,374,376],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,375,81],{"class":141},[135,377,378],{"class":144}," run\n",[135,380,381,383],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,382,88],{"class":141},[135,384,378],{"class":144},[135,386,387,389],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,388,96],{"class":141},[135,390,378],{"class":144},[135,392,393,395],{"class":137,"line":283},[135,394,100],{"class":141},[135,396,378],{"class":144},[12,398,399,400,403],{},"To run the vue-cli dev environment: ",[28,401,402],{},"nr dev",". Which equals:",[126,405,407],{"className":128,"code":406,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm run dev\nyarn run dev\npnpm run dev\nbun run dev\n",[28,408,409,419,427,435],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,410,411,413,416],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,412,81],{"class":141},[135,414,415],{"class":144}," run",[135,417,418],{"class":144}," dev\n",[135,420,421,423,425],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,422,88],{"class":141},[135,424,415],{"class":144},[135,426,418],{"class":144},[135,428,429,431,433],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,430,96],{"class":141},[135,432,415],{"class":144},[135,434,418],{"class":144},[135,436,437,439,441],{"class":137,"line":283},[135,438,100],{"class":141},[135,440,415],{"class":144},[135,442,418],{"class":144},[12,444,445,446,39],{},"Aside: if you want to specify a port, use ",[28,447,448],{},"nr dev --port 3000",[239,450,451],{"id":214},[28,452,214],{},[12,454,455,247,457,460,461,31,464,364,467,470],{},[28,456,214],{},[28,458,459],{},"execute"," — same as ",[28,462,463],{},"npx",[28,465,466],{},"dlx",[28,468,469],{},"nx create-nuxt-app example"," (the Nuxt.js create command) equals:",[126,472,474],{"className":128,"code":473,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npx create-nuxt-app example\nyarn dlx create-nuxt-app example\npnpx create-nuxt-app example\n",[28,475,476,486,497],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,477,478,480,483],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,479,463],{"class":141},[135,481,482],{"class":144}," create-nuxt-app",[135,484,485],{"class":144}," example\n",[135,487,488,490,493,495],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,489,88],{"class":141},[135,491,492],{"class":144}," dlx",[135,494,482],{"class":144},[135,496,485],{"class":144},[135,498,499,502,504],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,500,501],{"class":141},"pnpx",[135,503,482],{"class":144},[135,505,485],{"class":144},[12,507,508,509,511],{},"Note ",[28,510,100],{}," isn't included.",[239,513,514],{"id":219},[28,515,219],{},[12,517,518,247,520,523],{},[28,519,219],{},[28,521,522],{},"upgrade","! Maps to:",[126,525,527],{"className":128,"code":526,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm update\nyarn upgrade\nyarn up\npnpm update\n",[28,528,529,536,543,550],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,530,531,533],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,532,81],{"class":141},[135,534,535],{"class":144}," update\n",[135,537,538,540],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,539,88],{"class":141},[135,541,542],{"class":144}," upgrade\n",[135,544,545,547],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,546,88],{"class":141},[135,548,549],{"class":144}," up\n",[135,551,552,554],{"class":137,"line":283},[135,553,96],{"class":141},[135,555,535],{"class":144},[12,557,558,560],{},[28,559,100],{}," not included.",[239,562,563],{"id":224},[28,564,224],{},[12,566,567,247,569,572,573,576],{},[28,568,224],{},[28,570,571],{},"uninstall",". To remove pixi: ",[28,574,575],{},"nun pixi",". Maps to:",[126,578,580],{"className":128,"code":579,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm uninstall pixi\nyarn remove pixi\npnpm remove pixi\nbun remove pixi\n",[28,581,582,592,601,609],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,583,584,586,589],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,585,81],{"class":141},[135,587,588],{"class":144}," uninstall",[135,590,591],{"class":144}," pixi\n",[135,593,594,596,599],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,595,88],{"class":141},[135,597,598],{"class":144}," remove",[135,600,591],{"class":144},[135,602,603,605,607],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,604,96],{"class":141},[135,606,598],{"class":144},[135,608,591],{"class":144},[135,610,611,613,615],{"class":137,"line":283},[135,612,100],{"class":141},[135,614,598],{"class":144},[135,616,591],{"class":144},[12,618,619,620,623],{},"You can also remove global packages: ",[28,621,622],{},"unu -g @vue\u002Fcli",", which maps to:",[126,625,627],{"className":128,"code":626,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm uninstall -g @vue\u002Fcli\nyarn global remove @vue\u002Fcli\npnpm remove -g @vue\u002Fcli\nbun remove -g @vue\u002Fcli\n",[28,628,629,640,651,661],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,630,631,633,635,637],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,632,81],{"class":141},[135,634,588],{"class":144},[135,636,149],{"class":148},[135,638,639],{"class":144}," @vue\u002Fcli\n",[135,641,642,644,647,649],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,643,88],{"class":141},[135,645,646],{"class":144}," global",[135,648,598],{"class":144},[135,650,639],{"class":144},[135,652,653,655,657,659],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,654,96],{"class":141},[135,656,598],{"class":144},[135,658,149],{"class":148},[135,660,639],{"class":144},[135,662,663,665,667,669],{"class":137,"line":283},[135,664,100],{"class":141},[135,666,598],{"class":144},[135,668,149],{"class":148},[135,670,639],{"class":144},[239,672,673],{"id":229},[28,674,229],{},[12,676,677,247,679,682],{},[28,678,229],{},[28,680,681],{},"clean install"," — clears node_modules and reinstalls. Maps to:",[126,684,686],{"className":128,"code":685,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"npm ci\nyarn install --frozen-lockfile\npnpm install --frozen-lockfile\nbun install --no-save\n",[28,687,688,695,704,712],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,689,690,692],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,691,81],{"class":141},[135,693,694],{"class":144}," ci\n",[135,696,697,699,701],{"class":137,"line":269},[135,698,88],{"class":141},[135,700,325],{"class":144},[135,702,703],{"class":148}," --frozen-lockfile\n",[135,705,706,708,710],{"class":137,"line":276},[135,707,96],{"class":141},[135,709,325],{"class":144},[135,711,703],{"class":148},[135,713,714,716,718],{"class":137,"line":283},[135,715,100],{"class":141},[135,717,325],{"class":144},[135,719,720],{"class":148}," --no-save\n",[239,722,723],{"id":234},[28,724,234],{},[12,726,727,247,729,732],{},[28,728,234],{},[28,730,731],{},"agent alias",". I rarely use it and I'm not sure when it's useful, so I'll skip it. If I find a use case, I'll add it later.",[12,734,735,736,738,739,97,741,97,743,97,745,747],{},"That's pretty much all ",[28,737,162],{},"'s commands. Hopefully this frees you from juggling ",[28,740,81],{},[28,742,88],{},[28,744,96],{},[28,746,100],{}," and lets you focus on actual dev work.",[20,749,751],{"id":750},"powershell-issues","PowerShell issues",[12,753,754,755,757,758,760,761,763],{},"Windows PowerShell has a built-in ",[28,756,162],{}," command that's an alias for New-Item. So if you want to use ",[28,759,38],{},"'s ",[28,762,162],{},", you'll need to override it. Run this in PowerShell:",[126,765,767],{"className":128,"code":766,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"Remove-Item Alias:ni -Force -ErrorAction Ignore\n",[28,768,769],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,770,771,774,777,780,783],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,772,773],{"class":141},"Remove-Item",[135,775,776],{"class":144}," Alias:ni",[135,778,779],{"class":148}," -Force",[135,781,782],{"class":148}," -ErrorAction",[135,784,785],{"class":144}," Ignore\n",[12,787,788,789,791,792,39],{},"Before running this command, make sure you don't actually need PowerShell's built-in ",[28,790,162],{},". If you do need it, you'll have to adjust PowerShell config — see the ",[54,793,796],{"href":794,"rel":795},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.npmjs.com\u002Fpackage\u002F@antfu\u002Fni",[58],"official docs",[20,798,800],{"id":799},"references","References",[198,802,803],{},[201,804,805],{},[54,806,808],{"href":794,"rel":807},[58],"@antfu\u002Fni",[810,811,812],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":131,"searchDepth":269,"depth":269,"links":814},[815,816,818,820,830,831],{"id":22,"depth":269,"text":23},{"id":42,"depth":269,"text":817},"Wha